<section class="card">
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <details>
    <summary>Is a 50% frost date safe?</summary>
    <p>
      No. It represents the midpoint of historical freeze timing, not a guarantee.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Why not use hardiness zones?</summary>
    <p>
      Hardiness zones describe winter minimum temperatures, not spring freeze timing.
      Frost dates are more useful for planting schedules.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Does this apply in Canada?</summary>
    <p>
      Yes. Frost probability and 32°F (0°C) freeze thresholds apply across cold regions
      in both the U.S. and Canada.
    </p>
  </details>
</section>

